                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#193ra">f. 193ra</locus>
                           <desc>: Ownership note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#193ra">193ra</locus>: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ {ዘደብረማርያም። መካ [sic]}
                              ዘመጽአ፡ እምሀገረ፡ {መካን፡} ምስለ፡ አቡነ፡ መዝገበ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ዘሠረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ ወዘአውፅኦ፡ እምዝንቱ፡
                              ደብር፡ ዘሀገረ፡ {ማርያም፡} ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#193ra">193ra</locus>: This (is the) book of Dabra
                              Māryām Mäka(n) which came from the country of Kaswa with ʾabuna
                              Mazgaba Śǝllāse. He who steals it or erases (its text) or takes it out
                              of this church of the country of Māryām shall be excommunicated by the
                              authority of Peter and Paul.</quote> Written in red ink; the hand
                           appears to be the same as the one that executed rubrication. One name is
                           washed out. The names connected with the church of Makān Māryām were
                           added in pencil later, replacing the name ካስዋ፡ (an alternative
                           appellation of the monastery of Gunda Gunde) written originally. By
                           substituting the name of Kaswa with the name of Makān the scribe created
                           a contradiction in the note. ʾAbuna<note> Mazgaba Śǝllāse was the abbot
                              of Gunda Gunde monastery in the second half of the 17th – beginning of
                              the 18th cent. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#193ra">f. 193ra</locus>
                           <desc>: Inventory of books in possession of the church library.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> In Amharic, written in pen. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Pen trials: <locus target="#2v">2v</locus>.
 - Crude
                           notes: <locus target="#45r">45r</locus>, 55v, 173v (in the upper
                           margin).</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- White threads are inserted in the edges of some
                              folios (?).</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
